\begin_layout Paragraph
Firm-level Profitability Condition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{H}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{M}$
\end_inset

 be the output price-deflated wage rates for human labor and AI management labor,
 respectively.
 A firm produces only if it gains nonnegative profits:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
w_{H}\,l_{H}+w_{M}\,l_{M}\leq x.
\]

\end_inset

From 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:fixed_proportions"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

