\begin_layout Paragraph
1.
 Determining Bounds of 
\begin_inset Formula $g(.)$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
According to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:profitability_H"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 only firms whose 
\begin_inset Formula $l_{H}$
\end_inset

 is below 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{w}$
\end_inset

 will produce in equilibrium.
 This is an upper bound for 
\begin_inset Formula $g(.)$
\end_inset

.
 For the lower bound,
 first divide both sides of Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:macro_agg_prod"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{H}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{\tilde{H}}=\left(\theta_{H}+\frac{\theta_{AI}}{\tilde{H}^{\rho}}\right)^{\frac{1}{\rho}}.
\]

\end_inset

Define 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\tilde{H})=\left(\theta_{H}+\frac{\theta_{AI}}{\tilde{H}^{\rho}}\right)^{\frac{1}{\rho}}.$
\end_inset

 Observe that for positive 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{H}$
\end_inset

 the maximum of 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\tilde{H})$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{H}^{\frac{1}{\rho}}$
\end_inset

.
 To see this,
 consider the derivative:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f^{'}(\tilde{H})=-\theta_{AI}\tilde{H}^{-\rho-1}\left(\theta_{H}+\theta_{AI}\tilde{H}^{-\rho}\right)^{\frac{1-\rho}{\rho}}<0.
\]

\end_inset

Since 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{'}(\tilde{H})<0$
\end_inset

 everywhere 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\tilde{H})$
\end_inset

 is strictly decreasing over its entire domain and obtains its maximum at 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{H}\rightarrow0^{+}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho\leq0$
\end_inset

,
 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{H}$
\end_inset

 gets closer to zero the term 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\theta_{AI}}{\tilde{H}^{\rho}}$
\end_inset

 approaches zero and 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{H}$
\end_inset

 dominates the sum in parenthesis.
 Therefore,
 the maximum of 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\tilde{H})$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{H}^{\frac{1}{\rho}}$
\end_inset

.
 Considering that 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{\tilde{H}}=f(\tilde{H})$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{\tilde{H}}$
\end_inset

 is maximized at 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{H}^{\frac{1}{\rho}}$
\end_inset

 and thus 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{H}$
\end_inset

 achieves its minimum at 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}$
\end_inset

.
 This means that the lower bound of 
\begin_inset Formula $g(.)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
2.
 Rewriting Aggregate CES Production Function in Terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $g(.)$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Remember that the total industry-level output is 
\begin_inset Formula $1=\int_{0}^{\frac{1}{w}}\ g(t)\ dt$
\end_inset

 while the industry-aggregate variable input is 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{H}=\int_{0}^{\frac{1}{w}}\ t\ g(t)\ dt$
\end_inset

.
 Using these we can write 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:macro_agg_prod"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 as follows:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}}^{\frac{1}{w}}\ g(t)\ dt\ =\ \left(\theta_{H}\left(\int_{\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}}^{\frac{1}{w}}\ t\ g(t)\ dt\right)^{\rho}\ +\ \theta_{AI}\right)^{\frac{1}{\rho}}.
\]

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $x=\frac{1}{w}$
\end_inset

,
 and rewrite the above as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left(\int_{\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}}^{x}\ g(t)\ dt\right)^{\rho}\ =\ \theta_{H}\left(\int_{\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}}^{x}\ t\ g(t)\ dt\right)^{\rho}\ +\ \theta_{AI}.\label{eq:macro_prod_with_g}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Define
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\phi(x)=\int_{\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}}^{x}\ g(t)\ dt,\qquad\qquad\phi^{'}(x)=g(x),\label{eq:phi---1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\psi(x)=\int_{\theta_{H}^{-\frac{1}{\rho}}}^{x}\ t\ g(t)\ dt,\qquad\qquad\psi^{'}(x)=x\ g(x).\label{eq:psi---1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Thus,
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:macro_prod_with_g"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 turns into
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\phi^{\rho}=\theta_{H}\ \psi^{\rho}\ +\ \theta_{AI}.\label{eq:macro_prod_phi_psi}
\end{equation}

